solutions.content:
**Intuition**
`j` is read pointer and `i` is write pointer. We always write `s[j]` to `s[i]`.
If the last 3 characters in front of `i` is `"abc"`, we clean them by `i -= 3`.
In the end, return `i == 0`.
**Code**
```
class Solution {
public:
	bool isValid(string s) {
		int i = 0;
		int j = 0;
		int n = s.size();
		while (j < n)
		{
			s[i] = s[j];
			// checking is last three character is "abc" then we erase them means set i to i-3
			if (i >= 2 && s[i - 2] == 'a' && s[i - 1] == 'b' && s[i] == 'c')
			{
				i -= 3;
			}
			i++; j++;
		}
		return (i == 0);
	}
};
```
**Time Complexity : O(n)**
**Space Complexity : O(1)**

