Remove all occurances of abc from given string.
Basically transform s into t ie...convert given string into empty string.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Use STL find() to get the first occurance of "abc". Now divide the string into 2 parts. First part before the starting index of "abc" and the second part after "abc". 
Now call recursion for our new string without "abc". If string size becomes 0, then return true.


# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(N*N)
