# In Place Hashing
The core idea of this algorithm is to store 2 numbers together and extract them later. 

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/c3b8e6e8-d1b0-4743-ae35-39e3c0dfdc36_1675647493.4934015.jpeg)

5 and 3 for example: 3*10 +5 = 35 so whenever we want 5 its 35%5 and whenever we want 3 its 35/3.

But 10 is a small number and the given range is 1000, so we can use 10000 in place of 10.

1. Have 2 pointers first = 0 and second = n Iterate over the array.
2.  if i is even nums[i]=(nums[first++]%max)*max + nums[i];
3.  if i is odd nums[i]=(nums[second++]%max)*max + nums[i];
4. . Divide the entire array by 10000



