solutions.content:
# Intuition
We will increment the count after purchasing the cheapest ice cream available until coins are sufficient to buy the cheapest unpurchased ice-cream and decrement the value of coins by the amount of purchased ice-cream.

# Approach
1. Sort the vector.
2. Purchase the cheapest ice-cream if coins>=cheapest, i.e. coins-cheapest>=0 and if true then decrement the coins as coins=coins-costs[i].
3. Repeat step 2 until the all the ice-purschased or coins are sufficient.


# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n logn): because of sorting.



# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int maxIceCream(vector<int>& costs, int coins) {
