The logic is pretty simple:

1. Count the number of ice-creams which have a given cost, for all costs from 1 to 10^5.
2. Starting with the cheapest ice-creams, identify the maximum number you can buy without crossing your limit.
3. Adjust the limit that you have left, and update the answer.

```
class Solution {
    public int maxIceCream(int[] costs, int coins) {
        int[] counter = new int[100001];
        for(int i = 0 ; i < costs.length ; i++) counter[costs[i]]++;
        int answer = 0;
        for(int i = 1 ; i < 100001 ; i++) {
            if(counter[i] > 0) {
                int toUse = Math.min(coins / i, counter[i]);
                coins -= toUse * i;
                answer += toUse;
            }
        }
        return answer;
    }
}
```

