# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
To buy the maximum number of icecreams boy should start buying icecreams with less cost.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1. Sorting the costs array will do the work and sort the icecreams with lowest to highest prices.
2. Now start traversing the vector from left and each time boy buys a icecream, decrease the coins he have and increase the number of icecreams he have.
3. Once he left with coins less than cost of icecream, loop breaks and return maximum number of icecream he can have.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: `O(nlogn)`
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

