# Intuition
Here we can see that we need to buy ice creams bars from minimum cost to maximum cost i.e. if we sort the costs array or count the frequency of the costs we can easily calculate the no. of bars we can buy with the given coins.

# Approach
1. we can sort the array and count the bars we can buy and reduce the coins we have in each iteration. Time Complexity is O(nlogn).
2. We can count the frequency of the costs and get the no. of bars we can buy with the given coins in each iteration, also keep track of total count. Time Complexity is O(N + M). 

# Complexity
- Time complexity:O(N + M)

- Space complexity: O(M) where M is maximum cost

**Please upvote if you find this solution helpful. Thanks in Advance.**
# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int getMaxCost(int[] costs){
        // initialization
        int max = 0;

        // iterate over the costs
        for(int index = 0;index < costs.length;index++){
            max = Math.max(max, costs[index]);
        }

        return max;
    }
    public int maxIceCream(int[] costs, int coins) {
       // edge cases
        if(costs == null || costs.length == 0){
            return 0;
        }
        // initialization
        // get the max cost
        int maxCost = getMaxCost(costs);
        int countBars = 0;
        int[] countCosts = new int[maxCost + 1];

        // count the frequency of costs
        for(int cost : costs){
            countCosts[cost]++;
        }

        // iterate over the countCosts array
        for(int cost = 0;cost < countCosts.length;cost++){
            // when count is 0
            if(countCosts[cost] == 0){
                continue;
            }
            // when we have less coins
            if(coins < cost){
                break;
            }
            // buy possible no. ice cream bars
            int count = Math.min(countCosts[cost], coins / cost);
            coins -= count * cost;
            countBars += count;
        }

        return countBars;
    }
}
```

