# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Get the bar with minimum cost till coins are exhausted or cost of bar is greater than remaining coins 
# Approach 1
Sort the costs array
Start with minimum cost bar and check if we have enough coins to buy that bar. 
- If yes, buy the bar , increase answer by 1 ,and reduce remaining coins by the cost of bar. 
- If no, break the iteration as zero bars can be bought next as we have bars with higher costs later on.


# Complexity
- Time complexity : $$O(nlogn)$$
- Space complexity : $$O(1)$$
# Code
