class Solution {
public:
    int maxIceCream(vector<int>& costs, int coins) 
    {
        sort(costs.begin(),costs.end());

        int ans=0;
        for(int index=0 ; index<costs.size() ; index++)
        {
            if(coins-costs[index]>=0) ans++ , coins-=costs[index];
            else break;
        }    
        return ans;
    }
};
```
# Approach 2
Store the frequencies of all costs in a vector.
- Start by checking the frequency of minimum cost ie 1.
- Count the maximum number of bars that can be bought with remaining coins 
- If the cost of bar is greater than remaining coins , then break the iteration as no bar can be bought with remaining coins. 


# Complexity
- Time complexity :  $$O(n)$$
- Space complexity :  $$O(n)$$
