# Approach
The approach taken for this solution is to sort the array of costs in ascending order and then iterate through the array, adding up the costs of the ice cream cones as you go. If the sum of the costs exceeds the number of coins you have, the loop is terminated and the current number of ice cream cones is returned. If the loop completes, the final number of ice cream cones is returned.

# Complexity
